-- Gillard to Call Election in Second Half of Year, Focused Now on Mine Tax
-- Gemma Daley
-- 2010-06-28T22:48:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/gillard-to-call-election-in-second-half-of-year-focused-now-on-mine-tax.html

          
          
             Australian Prime Minister Julia
Gillard said her government was focused on a “genuine outcome”
for the planned 40 percent tax on resource profits. Gillard,
speaking to Australian Broadcasting Corp. radio in Melbourne,
said there would be an election in the second half of this year.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          June 29 (Bloomberg) -- Belinda Allen, an analyst at Colonial First State Global Asset Management, talks from Sydney with Bloomberg's Susan Li about the outlook for the Australian government's planned resources tax under the leadership of Prime Minister Julia Gillard.
     As soon as Gillard ousted Kevin Rudd as prime minister on June 24, she vowed to resolve a standoff over his proposed 40 percent mining tax on what he called "super" profits. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
